    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-02-02T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-02-02T07:00:00-05:00" n="69"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d69">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">883.00/1232: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-02-02T14:00:00+02:00"
                            >February 2, 1942—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 3:31 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>187. My 183, February 1, 6 p.m. It is reported but not yet officially announced
                    that the Prime Minister tendered his resignation shortly after noon today
                    following which the King received the British Ambassador on the latter’s urgent
                    demand. Latest indications were that the Ambassador would probably support the
                    return of the Wafd in preference to the formation of another weak coalition
                    excluding the Wafd and in order to forestall the nomination of a Palace–Aly
                    Maher candidate.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
